<p><a name="Books_based_on_personal_experiences" id="Books_based_on_personal_experiences"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=George_Orwell&amp;action=edit&amp;section=31" title="Edit section: Books based on personal experiences">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Books based on personal experiences</span></h3>
<p>While the substance of many of Orwell's novels, particularly <i>Burmese Days</i>, is drawn from his personal experiences, the following are works presented as narrative documentaries, rather than being fictionalised.</p>
<ul>
<li><i><a href="/wiki/Down_and_Out_in_Paris_and_London" title="Down and Out in Paris and London">Down and Out in Paris and London</a></i> (1933)</li>
<li><i><a href="/wiki/The_Road_to_Wigan_Pier" title="The Road to Wigan Pier">The Road to Wigan Pier</a></i> (1937)</li>
<li><i><a href="/wiki/Homage_to_Catalonia" title="Homage to Catalonia">Homage to Catalonia</a></i> (1938)</li>
</ul>
<p><a name="Essays" id="Essays"></a></p>
<h3><span class="editsection">[<a href="/w/index.php?title=George_Orwell&amp;action=edit&amp;section=32" title="Edit section: Essays">edit</a>]</span> <span class="mw-headline">Essays</span></h3>
